EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to offenders; extending the reversion date of the
appropriation made by the 81st Session of the Nevada
Legislature to the Department of Corrections for certain
costs related to the Nevada Offender Tracking
Information System; revising provisions governing credits
earned by an offender which reduce the term of
imprisonment of the offender; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 During the 2021 Legislative Session, the Legislature appropriated $1,436,720
2 to the Department of Corrections for the reintegration of the Offender Sentence
3 Management System into the Nevada Offender Tracking Information System. Any
4 remaining balance of that appropriation was required to be reverted to the State
5 General Fund on or before September 15, 2023. (Chapter 463, Statutes of Nevada
6 2021, at page 2875) During the 2023 Legislative Session, the Legislature extended
7 the reversion date to on or before September 19, 2025. (Section 84 of chapter 209,
8 Statutes of Nevada 2023, at page 1257) Section 2 of this bill extends the reversion
9 date to on or before September 17, 2027.
10 Existing law allows an offender to earn certain credits to reduce his or her
11 sentence of imprisonment. (NRS 209.432-209.453) During the 2023 Legislative
12 Session, the Legislature enacted Senate Bill No. 413, which established a revised
13 method for awarding credits to reduce the sentence of an offender that applied to an
14 offender sentenced to a crime committed: (1) on or after July 1, 2025; or (2) before
15 July 1, 2025, if the offender elected to be subject to the revised method. (Chapter
16 394, Statutes of Nevada 2023, at page 2308) Section 7 of this bill delays the
17 implementation of the revised method to July 1, 2026. Under section 3 of this bill,
