18 the revised method for awarding credits to reduce the sentence of an offender
19 applies to an offender sentenced to a crime committed: (1) on or after July 1, 2026;
20 or (2) before July 1, 2026, if the offender elects to be subject to the revised method.
21 Section 3 also: (1) permits an offender to earn additional credit for engaging in
22 exceptional meritorious service; (2) requires the Department to provide an offender
23 with certain information before the offender elects to be subject to the revised
24 method; and (3) makes various other changes relating to the revised method.
25 Sections 4-6 make conforming changes to reflect the change of date in section 3.
